description: A 5.4-tonne RAF bomb dropped in 1945 lies at the bottom of a busy Baltic shipping canal.
title: Polish divers tackle massive British WW2 bomb in Baltic
title_page: Polish divers tackle massive British WW2 bomb in Baltic - BBC News
maintext: About 750 residents have been evacuated from the area, near the port city of Swinoujscie, and the operation is expected to take five days.
